<h1 id="discrete-mathematics-1.0">DISCRETE MATHEMATICS 1.0</h1>
<p><strong>What is Discrete Mathematics?</strong> Math structures that are countable or otherwise distinct and separable.<br>
<strong>Ex.</strong> The output number 1.232419 is not discrete because the elements are separate.</p>
<p><strong>Four Main Discrete Math Topics</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Combinators</strong>, (the theory of ways things combine; in particular how to count these ways)</li>
<li><strong>Sequences</strong></li>
<li><strong>Symbolic Logic</strong></li>
<li><strong>Graph Theory</strong></li>
</ul>
